// EXPECTED REJECTION (release 0.01 decision, 2026-07-14; formerly
// drivers/cryptol_chacha20_iround_zero with goldens expecting
// successful translation). Companion to
// `cryptol_chacha20_core_iterate` — see that row's header for the
// full context.
//
// `iround n r = (iterate once r) @ n` reaches the same polymorphic
// `Prelude.fix`-over-`Stream` shape as `core`, so translation refuses
// `Prelude::Stream@core` — the named diagnostic this row pins. The
// property (`iround 0 r == r`, non-reflexive: the discharge must
// reduce `iterate once r @ 0` to `r`) is preserved verbatim so the
// pair keeps covering both the "translates at all" (core_iterate)
// and the "reduces correctly once proved" (this row) sides when the
// OP-3 successor design restores the translation path.

import "../../../../deps/cryptol-specs/Primitive/Symmetric/Cipher/Stream/chacha20.cry";

prove_print (offline_lean "test_cryptol_chacha20_iround_zero.eq")
  {{ \(r : [16][32]) -> iround 0 r == r }};
